Quest-2 TLDR. This is Long. Buckle up, please don't interrupt.
Day 1:
We found ourselves trapped in some tunnels - but with a new and unfamiliar face, a guy named FacePalm who told us he'd also been with the other group. Claimed Drunken Bard, a neutral.

We were told we had to reason a score of 12 for a "village-positive" outcome. If we played even supply numbers we had a 1/6 chance of a tunnel collapsing on us and killing us. We all expressed frustration about being trapped in the tunnels unable to see previous chat or our previous night actions.

We got some claims going, I'm a Gravedigger (having previously been a Drunk until night 4). HipsDontLie is a reviver who revived Covenment before we left, Spudcast eventually claimed Arcanist (Checks 2 players, gets told if they have the same tarot cards, or gets shown a random one that is not the same.).
GreatYear was pretty keen on lynching FacePalm, though the rest of us less so (This ultimately was the right call, we were all gifted potions of cleansing and inhebriation for sparing his life).

We managed to figure out how to look at previous night actions/chat (though it apparently didn't work for GreatYear), and once we were able to see our N4 night results I was able to share my dig of FoodCrimes as a Direwolf - to which GreatYear seemed to be fairly non-chalant about. Turns out they were lying about their previous role and were now claiming Illuminati Leader, and then later changed to Mason Leader (said he was trying to bait illuminati) with a recruit on Rocks who they claimed was an Agitator. (Rocks later confirmed this, but expressed concern at GreatYear missing their N4 chat.). They claimed their "Hound Card" check was actually bounced recruits that they just wanted to get lynched.

Swearwolves was able to see night chat from SandMoo - Claimed FlapWagon as a LostMason, Speculation of GreatYear being sketchy for denying the existence of multiple wolf clans, thought they were probably a Wulfkin Seer. Suggested not reviving Shapeshitter. Covenment as DS with KneeG as wolfpack. FoodCrimes still claiming good. Something about a Multiple clans fighting and wanting to get the wolfpack to bow down to them or that they can become the next wolf pack or something by killing the other clans/wolf pack. Wulfkin apparently have kill power. (I assume Covenment will have filled you all in on this as well anyway after their revive.)

SpudCast told us they had "Dove" as a conflicting card between Swearwolves (Should be Dove/Dove/Mag) and GreatYear (Should be Dove/Dove/Lab). (Also told us previous checks. Savvy+Owlder - Dove, Miner+Smug - Dove, Matt+Banana - Same Cards)

A few things started to look bad for GreatYear - Dove Card, GY Chat, failed Direwolf recruit (and not caring about the fact it should have killed them), (and eventually, missing N4 night chat with the Masons according to Rocks) - they were our Lead Lynch for most of the day. He speculated maybe he was redirected to a non-wolf and it was just bad luck on FoodCrimes.

GreatYear then mentioned to us about an Orb of Communication that his faction had and could talk to other people with it at night (4-8 others. Lots of shitposting apparently, people giving themselves 3-letter code names). Seems wolves had one and some others. Wolves had apparently shared the name of 6 different wulfkin clans on night 3 but GY continued to push against this during D4 speculating Deathmaw was a talent-tree choice.

GY continued to push back against his lynch for most of the day (He was responsible for killing wolves/wulfkin with his claim, claimed that it was perfectly normal mason play to get rid of rivals etc. Most lit person etc etc. "Hound" card is a certain lynch on someone so went with it) It was pointed out that the GY suggested wulfkins were fighting each other and this also made sense from that PoV. More speculation that he was just another wulfkin seer trying to kill others.

Rocks came on and confirmed for us the 6 clans the wolfpack mentioned: 	Deathmaws, Swiftclaws, Silvermanes, Redfangs, Sharptalons, Rendpack confirmed the orb, and that they had trolled a bit with it pretending to be multiple people and pretending to be a wolf clan to try and get intel (until people asked them questions they couldn't answer). Was concerned with GreatYear not showing up to night chat, but the Mason Sarg couldn't recruit in their place, so assumed they just weren't there rather than anything too bad.

As the day progressed, we discussed how we could reach our goal of 12 (Risky, needed everyone to play even numbers, and no one to really play negatives. "Safe" score was 5, unsafe was 15 or so. Assuming everyone had supplies, hadn't lied, was willing to play etc). Also risky, BananaDemon had a -6/+4 but hadn't shown up so we didn't know what they would play, and AnimeKirsch claimed no Quest Supplies at all becuase they had been stolen.

We ultimately decided to lynch AnimeKirsch for being idle and a terrible claim (We decided they were a Wulfkin seer trying to look like village). Also gave GreatYear a chance to prove themselves (talk in night chat with Rocks, Recruit SpudCast.)
Day 2:
We failed. Hard. 6/12. Ouch. SpudCast died in the night. F.

GreatYear claimed to be trapped by a cave-in which isolated and role blocked him at night and he had to make a choice to shoot his way out (-1) or dig his way out (+1). Picked dig, ended up digging Anime as a Wulfkin Seer in the process. My GY dig on Anime confirmed this.

No one else had this problem, everyone else chose their quest supplies as a way of contributing. (They auto picked a value, with the option of changing.) Concern that Banana might have auto-contributed their -6.
Banana was our lynch lead for a chunk of the day for their complete lack of contribution.

Rocks expressed concern about GreatYear not showing up for a second night in a row. Some speculation occurred that maybe GreatYear was actually a vamp recruit and that explained the ability to bounce a recruit on a wolf. But people thoguht maybe a bit far-fetched (too many evils), but that there was precedent for a lone-vamp in all the other big-exts to date.

Banana eventually showed up. Claimed Apothecary, claimed to have made some potions (the ones we got from the bard), passed their quest supplies to SpudCast, didn't notice ext-400-b thought their internet was just broken for ext-400 (didn't ask mod about it) etc. Generally one of the worst claims ever. Made GreatYear look lit again, that kinda bad.

Banana ALSO claimed an orb (Now letting us know it was called Whispering Orb). Though in continuing their worst-claim-ever, they claimed to only get it Night 2 and to never have spoken on it.  Ultimately though, people were somewhat trusting because of our trust in SpudCast and continued distrust of GreatYear, and the fact that the claim was *so bad*

Rocks came on and started pushing for a lynch on GreatYear (missing night chat 2 days in a row, DW recruit not killing, only left with -1 supplies, etc). Believes they have changed allegiance. More speculation about maybe a vamp recruit.
The group as a whole was fairly happy with either Banana or GreatYear as a lynch. We eventually went for GreatYear though as there was so much evidence against them.

In the final 10 minutes of the day GreatYear finally confessed to being recruited into the Deadmaws on Night 3. Rolled Wulfkin Seer, sniffed Banana as a wolfkin assassin. (Well, saw them as wulfkin but believes they killed SpudCast in the night). Claimed that the pact with the wolves merged their night-chats. Angry that Banana was getting away with the AFK-Meta. We still lynched them.
Day 3:
We apparently needed 8 points (we weren't told this). We failed again, with 6. Swearwolves was killed in the night. Then we got the choice to come here or go home.
